actions.comment:
Thanks for the report. Confirmed — both `SKGLView` and `SKCanvasView` in the Blazor package implement `IDisposable` directly without the standard `Dispose(bool)` pattern, preventing subclasses from extending disposal.

The fix would involve introducing `protected virtual void Dispose(bool disposing)` following the standard .NET pattern ([CA1063](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/fundamentals/code-analysis/quality-rules/ca1063)).

In the meantime, you can work around this by shadowing with `new`:

```csharp
public new void Dispose()
{
    // Your custom cleanup here
    base.Dispose();
}
```

Note that this won't work for polymorphic disposal through `IDisposable` references — the proper virtual pattern is the right long-term fix.
